{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"decorative-kingsize-degu","description":"## What\n\nReplace hand-maintained CLI command catalogs with a **generated** CLI command\nreference, so the highest-churn surface for human/LLM clients cannot go stale by hand.\nThis is the first of the two high-value interface inventories.\n\nTemplate the proven pattern: `scripts/gen_env_registry.py` writes a generated doc and\na CI drift gate (`.github/workflows/test.yml`, `gerrit-verify.yaml`) fails when the\ncommitted file diverges from regeneration.\n\n- Add `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new): derive the command list, usage strings,\n  and flags from the CLI registry / `--help` (single source of truth in\n  `src/rebar/_commands`), emit `docs/cli-reference.md` with a \"generated — do not edit\"\n  header.\n- Wire a drift gate into CI mirroring the env-registry gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/cli-reference.md` is generated from the CLI registry and marked generated.\n- [ ] A CI drift gate fails the build if the committed reference is out of date.\n- [ ] Adding/removing a CLI command or flag changes the generated output (verified).\n\nFiles: `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new), `docs/cli-reference.md` (new/generated),\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`.","id":"e866-0bdb-94e3-41e6","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":2,"tags":["docs","generated","p1"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P1: Generate the CLI command reference (generator + drift gate)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814580647666001,"uuid":"b59c6ec7-f73a-4c07-9534-f7f7f1b84991"}